{"type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Layered Artifact + Plugin Toolkits\n      Recommended. Three interconnected systems that compose cleanly.\n      \n        Layer 1 — Concern Detection Engine\n        Extensible keyword→category registry scans shape.md. Categories: web-visual, game-visual, print-layout, etc. Each category maps to specialist activation + tool family. New categories added by dropping a config file.\n        \n        Layer 2 — Design Artifact Lifecycle\n        ridgeline design command creates project-level .ridgeline/design.md via interactive shaping (reuses shaper pattern). Specifier's visual specialist reads project design + shape, produces feature-level design section. Builder/reviewer inherit both layers.\n        \n        Layer 3 — Visual Tool Families (Plugin-based)\n        Each tool family is a Ridgeline plugin: plugin/web-visual/ bundles Playwright, axe-core, CSS analyzers, pixelmatch. Future: plugin/game-visual/ bundles asset validators, scene graph tools. Concern detection activates the right plugin. Reviewer invokes tools from the active plugin.\n      \n      \n        ProsEach system is independently useful and testableNew tool families don't touch core pipeline codeConcern categories are data, not codePlugin architecture already exists in Ridgeline\n        ConsThree systems to build and coordinatePlugin packaging adds complexity for tool dependencies (Playwright binary, etc.)","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1775937221867}
